548.source:
function doAboutST72() { // this.doAboutST72()
    var about = "Smalltalk-72 was the first operating Smalltalk system.  While its syntax " +
        "was almost as simple as that of LISP, its message stream model of evaluation " +
        "allowed a modern style of object-oriented programming to be implemented and " +
        "developed even within the bounds of what today would be called a " +
        "minuscule environment (128k).  Those who are interested in the details of this " +
        "language are referred to <yet to be written paper>, but much of it will become " +
        "obvious from reading the original Instruction Manual (see button) and playing " +
        "with the system here.\n" +
        "\tUse the backslash key '\\' to type the Smalltalk do-it character\n" +
        "\tMore key info needed?\n"
    this.world().addTextWindow(
        {title: "About Smalltalk-72", 
        position: this.worldPoint(pt(-30, 30)),
        extent: pt(555,250),
        acceptInput: false,
        content: about}
    );
	

}

551.source:
function doAboutEmulation() { // this.doAboutEmulation()
    var about = "In order to make it easy for students to work on Smalltalk once " +
        "a week, the system was built to save its entire state as a memory dump " +
        "(called a .SV, or 'save' file) that could be restarted at a later time " +
        "with every bit (programs as well as display content) exactly " +
        "restored.  Just as this approach facilitated resumption after a week of " +
        "absence, so it also enables resumption after forty years of disuse!\n\n" +
        "This emulation is an object in the Lively Web development environment " +
        "ith an entire save file read into a single array called this.mem.  A " +
        "handful of methods serve to emulate the Nova instruction set, and a " +
        "Canvas object displays the parts of memory that appeared on the ALTO " +
        "screen, and pass keyboard and mouse events to the simulated memory just " +
        "as they were in the Alto hardware.\n\n" +
        "If you are interested in how this works, choose 'Show Nova'.  The " +
        "display will disappear and you will see a modest Nova programmer's " +
        "dashboard.  To return to the Smalltalk level, choose 'Show Smalltalk'.  " +
        "When working with the ALTO Nova, the emulator is in single-instruction " +
        "mode;  when you return to Smalltalk the emulator executes thousands of " +
        "instructions and then updates the display."
    this.world().addTextWindow(
        {title: "About this Emulation", 
        position: this.worldPoint(pt(-60, 60)),
        extent: pt(555,400),
        acceptInput: false,
        content: about}
    );
	

}

557.source:
function doAboutLively() { // this.doAboutST72()
    var about = "This emulation of Smalltalk-72 on the ALTO is written in Lively Web.  " +
        "Lively is a development environment in which it is easy to assemble an " +
        "application and program its details while it is running so that you " +
        "see the effects of your creations and changes immediately.  " +
        "A Lively creation can be stored and shared as a web page, and that is " +
        "how you are able to run this historical reconstruction in your browser.\n\n" +
        "If you are feeling courageous, use cmd-click on the beige panel, and click " +
        "the item 'E' in the halo that appears.  This opens a Lively script editor " +
        "that will allow you to inspect (and change) all the code.\n\n" +
        "Visit Lively-Web.org to find out more about using Lively."
    this.world().addTextWindow(
        {title: "About Lively-Web", 
        position: this.worldPoint(pt(-90, 90)),
        extent: pt(555,250),
        acceptInput: false,
        content: about}
    );
	

}
